Tom: What are you going to do this summer, Anna?
Anna: I'm going to visit my grandparents in the countryside.
Tom: That sounds relaxing. How long will you stay?
Anna: For two weeks. I'll help my grandpa on the farm.
Tom: Sounds fun, but also hard work!
Anna: It is, but I enjoy it. What about you?
Tom: I'm going to a summer camp because I want to make new friends.
Anna: That's a great idea. What will you do there?
Tom: We'll go hiking and swimming every day.
Anna: I hope we both have a wonderful summer!
